Yeah, but that was a while ago.

587
00:52:48,042 --> 00:52:50,659
我不知道，如果我想要告诉你关于这个...
I don't know if I want to talk about it.

588
00:52:53,256 --> 00:52:54,597
来吧，杰克
Come on, Jack.

589
00:52:54,665 --> 00:52:57,599
你那么麻烦用你的小红手推车拖到这里...
You dragged it all the way down here
in your little red wagon.

590
00:52:57,673 --> 00:52:59,876
说吧...告诉我吧...
Come on, just tell me about it.

591
00:53:03,560 --> 00:53:07,902
我做的这个是用尼古拉·特斯拉的原始设计
I built it based on the inventor
Nikola Tesla's original designs.

592
00:53:09,000 --> 00:53:10,887
是一个空气变压器...
It's an air transformer...

593
00:53:11,111 --> 00:53:14,688
由主线圈和副线圈调整共振
with primary and secondary coils
that are tuned to resonate.

594
00:53:15,303 --> 00:53:18,052
主要就是一个升压变压器
It's basically a step-up transformer...

595
00:53:18,119 --> 00:53:22,373
它可以把相对低压高强电流转换为高压弱电流...
which converts relatively low-voltage
high current to high-voltage low current...

596
00:53:22,439 --> 00:53:24,129
用高频的
at high frequencies.

597
00:53:25,894 --> 00:53:27,322
你还记得吗？...
Do you remember...

598
00:53:27,399 --> 00:53:31,075
我们还是小孩子的时候
你有一个小芭比娃娃的镜子
when we were kids,
you had a little Barbie makeup mirror?

599
00:53:31,653 --> 00:53:33,441
嗯，我记得那个
Yeah, I remember that.

600
00:53:33,829 --> 00:53:36,316
那个镜子有一个小荧光
It had a little fluorescent light on it?

601
00:53:37,157 --> 00:53:39,774
是尼古拉·特斯拉发明了荧光
Nikola Tesla invented fluorescent light.

602
00:53:40,549 --> 00:53:43,298
如果没有他，我们没有交流电...
Without him,
we wouldn't have alternating current...

603
00:53:43,365 --> 00:53:46,812
没有收音机，电视，X光技术...
radio, television, x-ray technology...

604
00:53:47,813 --> 00:53:51,358
没有感应电机，粒子束流，激光
induction motors, particle beams, lasers.

605
00:53:51,556 --> 00:53:54,687
如果没有他，这些什么都没有。
None of that would even exist,
if it weren't for him.

606
00:53:54,756 --> 00:53:56,610
或者，也没有特斯拉乐队～
Or the rock band, Tesla.

607
00:53:59,716 --> 00:54:00,828
搞笑！！
Funny.

608
00:54:03,075 --> 00:54:04,962
特斯拉绝对是一个天才
Tesla was a true genius.

609
00:54:05,539 --> 00:54:10,045
如果我们更多关注他的创意，这世界一定会变得更加美好。
If we had paid more attention to his ideas,
the world would be a much better place.

610
00:54:10,115 --> 00:54:13,213
我们人人都能享用免费的通讯技术，免费的的交通运输...
We'd have free mass communication,
free transportation...

611
00:54:13,315 --> 00:54:14,875
人人都有取之不尽用之不完的能源。
free energy for everyone.

612
00:54:14,979 --> 00:54:19,556
就是因为他想造福人类使用免费能源，使得那些人排挤他诽谤他...令他无法继续...
That's why they discredited him in the end.
For free energy.

613
00:54:20,546 --> 00:54:24,222
他能感知到，地球是一个声音共振的导体。
He perceived the Earth
as a conductor of acoustical resonance.

614
00:54:28,257 --> 00:54:30,045
多美好的想法啊
What a beautiful idea.

615
00:54:33,921 --> 00:54:37,149
那，杰克，你要给我看看它工作起来什么样吗？
So, Jack, are you going to show me
how the coil works?

616
00:54:38,400 --> 00:54:39,926
好，没问题
Yeah, all right.

617
00:54:42,976 --> 00:54:44,568
你得带上这个
You'll need these.

618
00:55:11,710 --> 00:55:14,131
－好了，你准备好了吗？梅格
－我准备好了
- All right, you ready, Meg?
- I'm ready.

619
00:55:43,931 --> 00:55:46,069
该死的，出故障了
Damn it. Something went wrong.

620
00:55:47,419 --> 00:55:49,109
没事，照样牛逼
It was cool, though.

621
00:55:50,011 --> 00:55:53,272
对，但是不应该停啊
它应该继续运转的啊
Yeah, but it wasn't supposed to stop.
It was supposed to keep working.

622
00:55:53,339 --> 00:55:55,226
我不知道出什么问题了
I don't know what happened.

623
00:55:55,323 --> 00:55:57,689
我觉得，也许是你的电容器冒烟儿了
I think maybe you blew a capacitor?

624
00:55:58,011 --> 00:56:00,399
没有，我的电容器没冒烟儿，梅格
No, I didn't blow a capacitor, Meg.

625
00:56:03,258 --> 00:56:05,145
也许应该断掉你的GFI（插座）
Maybe it tripped your GFI.

626
00:56:05,722 --> 00:56:08,023
对，你的接地漏电保护插座！
Yeah, your Ground Fault Interrupter.

627
00:56:08,089 --> 00:56:11,384
嘿！我知道什么是插座
不是那个的问题
Yeah, I know what a GFI is.
That's not what happened.

628
00:56:12,569 --> 00:56:14,357
你用不着这么激动突然打断我...
You don't have to snap at me.

629
00:56:29,239 --> 00:56:35,646
我觉得，也许是你的火花间隙太大
导致它在火花线圈振动的时候出了问题
I think maybe the spark gaps
are too far apart on your spark coil vibrator.

630
00:56:42,647 --> 00:56:44,469
对，有可能
Yeah, that could be it.

631
00:56:45,943 --> 00:56:47,120
我猜
I guess.

632
00:56:50,742 --> 00:56:52,564
对对，就是，就是那儿的问题
Yeah, it is. That's it.

633
00:56:53,589 --> 00:56:56,817
你是对的，我没检查那里
You're right about that.
I didn't check that earlier.

634
00:57:09,364 --> 00:57:11,752
那我现在回家检查一下去
I'm gonna go home and check it out.

635
00:57:13,524 --> 00:57:16,273
－你明天去不去打保龄球？
－嗯，我会过去
- Are you going to go bowling tomorrow?
- Yeah, I'll be there.

636
00:57:16,340 --> 00:57:18,379
那好，我们在那见
All right, I'll see you there.

637
00:58:04,209 --> 00:58:07,023
地球是一个声音共振的导体！
Earth as a conductor
of acoustical resonance.

638
00:58:24,719 --> 00:58:26,020
表亲？

638
00:58:28,719 --> 00:58:31,020
喂，是谁？
Hello, who is this?

639
00:58:31,534 --> 00:58:34,697
劳拉，嗨～我是阿尔弗雷德·莫里纳，找史蒂夫·库根
Laura. Hi, this is Alfred Molina
for Steve Coogan.

640
00:58:39,181 --> 00:58:41,155
M-O-L-I-N-A.

641
00:58:43,405 --> 00:58:44,866
艺人，对
The actor, yes.

642
00:58:46,669 --> 00:58:49,254
我想再次确认一下史蒂夫是不是...
I was just double-checking that Steve...

643
00:58:49,484 --> 00:58:51,720
他是，非常好
He is. Great, okay.

644
00:58:51,949 --> 00:58:54,436
以防万一，我的手机号码是... ...
Just in case you need it,
my cell phone number...

645
00:58:54,508 --> 00:58:55,620
喂？
Hello?

646
00:59:05,548 --> 00:59:08,002
－你好，阿尔弗雷的
－史蒂夫，你好！
- Hello, Alfred.
- Steve, hello.

647
00:59:08,843 --> 00:59:12,104
嗨，我很高兴你能来
请坐吧
Hi. I'm so glad you could make it.
Please sit down.

648
00:59:12,747 --> 00:59:16,837
我刚才还给你的助理劳拉打电话，问一下你是不是在路上
I was just talking to Laura, your assistant,
seeing if you were on your way here.

649
00:59:16,907 --> 00:59:18,368
－我来了
－棒极了！
- I'm here.
- Fantastic.

650
00:59:18,442 --> 00:59:21,059
恕我冒昧的点了茶给你
I took the liberty of ordering some tea.

651
00:59:21,706 --> 00:59:23,167
要我给你倒上吗？
Shall I be mother?

652
00:59:23,722 --> 00:59:26,110
噢，没关系。我可以自己来
That's okay, I'll be my own mother.

653
00:59:26,473 --> 00:59:28,360
这有为你点的牛奶
Some milk there for you.

654
00:59:29,546 --> 00:59:30,723
正宗的茶！
Real tea.

655
00:59:32,361 --> 00:59:33,571
很难寻的
It's hard to come by.

656
00:59:33,673 --> 00:59:38,113
我曾幻想如果我能赢得金球奖或者奥斯卡小金人...
I have this fantasy where if I ever won
a Golden Globe or an Academy Award...

657
00:59:38,217 --> 00:59:42,526
那我一定利用好这个机会，教美国佬怎么做一杯像样的茶
I'd use the opportunity to tell the Yanks
how to make a decent cup of tea.

658
00:59:43,912 --> 00:59:46,399
－为了这杯正宗的茶！
－干杯！
- Here's to a good cup of tea.
- Cheers.

659
00:59:51,112 --> 00:59:53,446
我喜欢你的大衣
I love your coat.

660
00:59:54,311 --> 00:59:56,198
对啊，这可是维维安·韦斯特伍德
Yeah, it's Viv Westwood.

661
00:59:58,919 --> 01:00:01,471
我特别喜欢英国的设计师
I've got a weakness for British designers.

662
01:00:01,543 --> 01:00:03,746
我不知道美国的设计师是...
I don't know what it is
about American designers.

663
01:00:03,847 --> 01:00:06,018
他们太保守了
They're just too safe.

664
01:00:07,302 --> 01:00:11,076
那你穿这样不热吗？外面将近29摄氏度呢
Aren't you going to be a little bit warm?
It's about 85 outside.

665
01:00:12,038 --> 01:00:14,404
啊不不不，我出门就脱了...
No, I take it off when I go out.

666
01:00:15,173 --> 01:00:17,376
在这，只是因为空调的原因
It's just the air conditioning.

667
01:00:24,325 --> 01:00:28,797
－那你在洛杉矶多久了？
－我们在这大概有7年了
- So how long have you been living in LA?
- We've been here about seven years.

668
01:00:29,285 --> 01:00:30,845
我们爱死这儿了
We love it here.

669
01:00:32,516 --> 01:00:34,206
旅游参观的话不错
I do love visiting LA.

670
01:00:34,276 --> 01:00:38,716
但我一直在说，洛杉矶虽好，但此地不易久留
But I always say, it's a great place to visit,
it's an even nicer place to leave.

671
01:00:40,804 --> 01:00:42,145
那些棕榈树...
The palm trees...

672
01:00:42,468 --> 01:00:44,856
那些棕榈树真他妈碍眼...
Palm trees annoy the fuck out of me.

673
01:00:45,668 --> 01:00:48,515
嗯嗯，不是所有人都像我一样喜欢这里
It's not for everybody. I like it here.

674
01:00:48,579 --> 01:00:51,612
本来是因为工作上的事儿才来这里的
I came out here for the work and stuff.

675
01:00:54,755 --> 01:00:57,307
我终于可以见到你咧！
It's great to finally meet you.

676
01:00:57,539 --> 01:01:00,473
我应该告诉你，其实我是你的超级粉丝儿...
I've got to say I'm a huge fan of your stuff...

677
01:01:00,546 --> 01:01:02,847
看过你所有的电视还有喜剧片什么的...
all the stuff you've done on TV,
the comedy stuff.

678
01:01:02,914 --> 01:01:07,615
我有你所有的录像带，都是从老家发过来的，实在是太棒了！
I've got all the tapes.
I get them sent over. It's fantastic.

679
01:01:08,258 --> 01:01:09,435
谢谢你的支持
Thank you.

680
01:01:15,553 --> 01:01:19,382
我也听说过你很多...
Likewise, I'm certainly very aware of you.

681
01:01:19,649 --> 01:01:20,859
哇噢～
Great.

682
01:01:23,361 --> 01:01:25,881
我看过你演的电视剧
I saw that TV series you did.

683
01:01:27,072 --> 01:01:28,566
啊～你看过？
Yeah, you saw that?

684
01:01:28,864 --> 01:01:30,838
对，很有意思
Yeah. Interesting.

685
01:01:32,384 --> 01:01:34,871
－但是已经取消播放了...
－对，我听说了
- We got canceled.
- Yeah, I heard that.

686
01:01:36,288 --> 01:01:38,524
喜剧表演是非常难以拿捏的...
Comedy's such a difficult thing.

687
01:01:44,223 --> 01:01:48,794
你的职业前景一片光明，如日中天，你现在是炙手可热的大明星。
Your career seems to be going terribly well.
You've got a lot of heat at the moment.

688
01:01:51,422 --> 01:01:53,080
你是因为这个在这吗？
Is that why you're here?

689
01:01:53,150 --> 01:01:57,372
在这有很多的宣传和见面会，这很好
The merry-go-round of meetings. It's nice.

690
01:01:57,438 --> 01:02:01,845
终于引起人们的关注了，这是好的开端
People are finally starting
to take a bit of notice, which is great.

691
01:02:01,918 --> 01:02:04,535
－你的见面会有意思吗？
－当然
- Are you meeting on anything interesting?
- Yeah.

692
01:02:13,181 --> 01:02:17,687
我必须让你知道，你太出色了...
I've got to say you were just fantastic...

693
01:02:17,885 --> 01:02:22,488
在《24小时》当中，毫无疑问...
《24小时狂欢派对》给人非常非常深刻的印象
in 24 Hour. No, seriously,
24 Hour Party People was just a knockout.

694
01:02:22,556 --> 01:02:25,337
－我的意思是，杰出的，巨作！
－谢谢
- I mean, brilliant. Great work.
- Thank you.

695
01:02:26,075 --> 01:02:28,049
真的是非常杰出的。是...
Really brilliant. It was...

696
01:02:29,500 --> 01:02:31,092
而且影评...
And the reviews...

697
01:02:31,515 --> 01:02:33,783
太尼玛好了！！！！
They were pretty fucking great.

698
01:02:33,851 --> 01:02:36,468
都给我震了！因为，是...
I was amazed because it was...

699
01:02:36,538 --> 01:02:39,985
我不觉得很多人参照了解过这个的文化...
I didn't think many people would get
all the cultural references.

700
01:02:40,059 --> 01:02:42,960
比如，80年代早期，当时曼彻斯特的乐坛
Sort of, Manchester, early '80s,
the whole music scene.

701
01:02:43,034 --> 01:02:44,244
令你十分惊讶
You'd be surprised.

702
01:02:44,346 --> 01:02:48,436
但是，很多人没有什么可参照的，因为...
But a lot of people didn't have any kind
of reference to make to it because...

703
01:02:48,858 --> 01:02:50,865
虽然，他们知道关于那里的乐队...
They know about the bands over here...

704
01:02:50,970 --> 01:02:55,126
但是，这个...你的角色，和他的电视节目...
but the whole thing, your character,
and his running the TV show...

705
01:02:55,193 --> 01:02:57,015
你想来根烟吗？
Do you want a cigarette?

706
01:02:57,081 --> 01:02:59,895
－抱歉，这是法国的
－没，没事没事，谢谢
- Sorry, they're French.
- No, that's okay. Thanks.

707
01:03:06,137 --> 01:03:07,959
等会儿再抽
I'll save it for later.

708
01:03:09,816 --> 01:03:10,863
好吧
Okay.

709
01:03:20,311 --> 01:03:23,507
那，劳拉说了...
So, Laura said that...

710
01:03:25,047 --> 01:03:29,356
你很迫切的要见我，但她没说是关于什么的
you were really keen to meeting.
She wouldn't tell me what it was.

711
01:03:29,463 --> 01:03:32,975
我不要给你打电话说这些，因为那样听起来很奇怪
I didn't want to say it over the phone
because it would've sounded weird.

712
01:03:33,046 --> 01:03:35,915
我能明白劳拉的感觉，非常突然的...
I can imagine how she thought.
This was coming out of nowhere.

713
01:03:35,990 --> 01:03:38,161
给她打电话，她也不知道我是谁，可能亚当没告诉她
I phone her up,
and she doesn't know me from Adam.

714
01:03:38,230 --> 01:03:40,913
我说“我必须要跟史蒂夫·库根通话”
I said, "I must talk to Steve Coogan."

715
01:03:41,142 --> 01:03:42,832
但是我要见到你
But I wanted to see you in person.

716
01:03:42,902 --> 01:03:45,073
后来我发现你会在这里停留几天...
When I found out you'd be here
for a few days...

717
01:03:45,141 --> 01:03:47,890
我觉得这是最好的机会告诉你...
I thought this was the perfect opportunity
to let you know...

718
01:03:47,989 --> 01:03:50,639
无论如何，闲话少说...
Anyway, I'll get right to it.

719
01:03:51,668 --> 01:03:53,675
对关于这个，我相当的激动...
I'm so excited about this.

720
01:03:54,581 --> 01:03:56,588
容我捋一捋... ...
Let me try and put it in context.

721
01:03:58,900 --> 01:04:01,517
我一直非常热衷于历史...
I've always had a big passion for history...

722
01:04:01,588 --> 01:04:03,562
和人文...
and people's lives...

723
01:04:03,635 --> 01:04:08,206
我相信，任何小事儿都是遵从A到B的原则...
and all the little events
of how you get from A to B...

724
01:04:09,043 --> 01:04:11,693
包括人们生活时的任何小细节...
and all the small details in people's lives...

725
01:04:11,764 --> 01:04:15,025
这种小细节满是诗情画意...
that are kind of really full of epic qualities.

726
01:04:15,475 --> 01:04:18,376
我做了很多关于这个的研究...
So I've been doing all this research and...

727
01:04:21,459 --> 01:04:22,887
得到了这些...
I've come up with this.

728
01:04:22,994 --> 01:04:26,408
到什么阶段了...
已经准备就绪还是要再继续处理你的研究？
And what state is...
Is it greenlit or is it just a treatment?

729
01:04:26,514 --> 01:04:28,008
到什么阶段了？
What stage is it?

730
01:04:29,170 --> 01:04:31,657
太对不起了，天呐！这太尴尬了
I'm sorry. God, it's so embarrassing.

731
01:04:31,825 --> 01:04:35,469
这不是...这不是工作
跟工作没有关系...
It's not some... This isn't work.
It's got nothing to do with work.

732
01:04:35,537 --> 01:04:37,359
这不是一个“项目”
It's not a project.

733
01:04:37,426 --> 01:04:41,255
我做的是关于血统祖谱的研究，然后我得到...
I did some genealogical research,
and I came across...

734
01:04:41,649 --> 01:04:42,957
我发现的就是...
What I discovered was...

735
01:04:43,025 --> 01:04:44,780
－库根先生？
－是我，什么事？
- Mr. Coogan?
- Yes?

736
01:04:44,849 --> 01:04:46,474
－真的是你吗？
－是我！
- It is you, isn't it?
- It is, yes.

737
01:04:46,544 --> 01:04:49,642
－我是你庞大的粉丝儿
－你不是那么“庞大”
- I'm such a huge fan.
- You're not that huge.

738
01:04:50,960 --> 01:04:52,683
只在关键部位是。
Only where it counts.

739
01:04:53,616 --> 01:04:56,681
－可以麻烦你给我一个签名吗？
－当然，当然
- Could I bother you for an autograph?
- Absolutely.

740
01:04:56,880 --> 01:04:58,984
－太棒了～
－已经有人认识我了
- Great.
- I've been recognized.

741
01:04:59,311 --> 01:05:01,001
